Is it just me or does that quote from Josh still look like he is making the assumption that Thesp is reading emo as town while it looks (and now confirmed) that it is more of a null/scum read?<br>
<br>
@Josh - Why not vote emo yesterday?

@EmoGirl:  If you don't post content soon, this vote is going to move to you.<br>
<br>
<span class="bbvote" title="This is an official vote.">VOTE: Luca Blight</span>

I'm doing that too, Luca. Gotta convince me to vote someone else, not make me feel self conscious.<br>
<br>
@Josh I mean I explained Thesp in the post above yours. Also why should we lynch your perceived SK reads instead of just good ol' scumreads today?

Okay, sorry for triple post.  I meant to say one more thing to Llama:<br>
<br>
@Llama:  Do you think that Josh will flip doc?  Do you subscribe to Lynch All Liars as a general policy?

I actually agree with Luca here.<br>
<br>
@Egg - If you agree that scum was voting Josh, do you think they more likely would have waited to try and use deadline as a reason or try stick to the wagon?

@Lissa - looking over your "catchup post" I see you using a bunch of poe and vca as to how you arrived at TDA being scum, but i don't really see any reasoning behind it.  Why do you think TDA is scum?<br>
<br>
<br>
@The dude - I find it kind of odd that you question lissa to explain why she thinks people are town, but don't question her to explain why she put you at L-1 with almost no reasoning...

@Lissa - I meant no-kill as in they didn't kill.<br>
<br>
Obviously I, as Town, don't know the circumstances behind it...I suspect you do.
